      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RARE EARTH (2) box seated before sticking on well to finish 5 lengths away in second (22.70) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Can measure up this time. KUNG FU ETHICS (1) was an impressive last start winner, scoring an enormous 22.37 win and a new Best time this course and distance. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. TROPICAL ETHICS (4) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 22.50 beating GANGSTER GORT. Jumping from the pinch draw but likes the trip. Won at her only start from this draw. Leading player again. SIR TICK (8) has won at this course and distance – sure to figure prominently.",
